elementary Dark is a soft and subtle dark theme based on the higly popular elementary theme by DanRabbit - http://danrabbit.deviantart.com/art/elementary-gtk-theme-83104033

The theme is compatible with the latest GTK 3.4 and uses the Unico engine. It also includes the elementary Dark GTK 2.0 theme using Murrine engine.

---

Ubuntu users can install elementary Dark from our themes PPA using the following commands,

sudo add-apt-repository ppa:satyajit-happy/themes
sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install elementary-dark-theme

---

Installation Instructions for other distros:

Extract the zip file to the themes directory i.e. "~/.themes/" or "/usr/share/themes/"

Use Gnome Tweak tool to choose the theme, or run the following commands in Terminal,

gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.interface gtk-theme "elementary Dark"

gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.wm.preferences theme "elementary Dark"

---

Note:

If you use Gnome 3.2, download the theme from launchpad https://launchpad.net/~satyajit-happy/+archive/themes/+files/elementary-dark-theme_2012.01.30-0~satya164~oneiric.tar.gz

This theme is not compatible with old Gnome 3.0.

